These are the existing database tools that Hither is using under the hood
and/or borrowing ideas from:

- Django

  Django is a very popular Python MVC framework, with a builtin ORM and solid
  migration tools and stratagies. The migration doc is here:

  * https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.8/topics/migrations/

- ActiveRecord

  ActiveRecord is the popular Ruby ORM that Rails uses.

- DBIx::Class

  DBIx::Class is the popular Perl ORM used by Dancer and others.

- DBIx::Class::DeploymentHandler

  This is a toolset for handling DBIx::Class database migrations.

  * https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Class::DeploymentHandler
  * https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Class::DeploymentHandler::DeployMethod::SQL::Translator

- SQL::Translator

  A general purpose database munging tool written in Perl. Includes a command
  line tool for some operations.

  * https://metacpan.org/pod/SQL::Translator
  * https://metacpan.org/pod/SQL::Translator::Manual
  * https://metacpan.org/pod/SQL::Translator::Parser::DBIx::Class

